{"id":14880758,"mediaExerciseId":"8328b85b-f872-4963-9a3a-7008aaa7deef","exerciseName":"7","chapterName":"2","chapterTitle":"Financial Statements, Taxes, and Cash Flow","groupId":612265,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":43,"solutions":[{"id":5901332,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"This exercise requires us to compute for the change in NWC of Dream Inc..","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":28,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/18/363290140e4b3fd0e01eae4d2cc3874d/4436776548e4acafce42ea5b7aa78de3/lateximg_large.png","width":993},"regular":{"height":15,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/18/363290140e4b3fd0e01eae4d2cc3874d/4436776548e4acafce42ea5b7aa78de3/lateximg.png","width":496}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Let's first define Net Working Capital and Change in Net Working Capital.\n\n- **Net Working Capital** is the difference between a company's current assets and its current liabilities.\n\n- **Change in Net Working Capital** is the change in current asset minus the change in current liabilities. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":179,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/18/363290140e4b3fd0e01eae4d2cc3874d/9b70a40d6ee0fea5f34d7e82fe012ee7/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":91,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/18/363290140e4b3fd0e01eae4d2cc3874d/9b70a40d6ee0fea5f34d7e82fe012ee7/lateximg.png","width":497}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"Change in Net Working Capital (NWC) is computed as follows:\n\n$$ \\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Change in NWC} &= \\text{Ending NWC} - {\\text{Beginning NWC}}\\\\[1pt]\n\\end{aligned}$$\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":104,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/18/363290140e4b3fd0e01eae4d2cc3874d/e86cf2090d3eec989c5bb68ae6d3b0e6/lateximg_large.png","width":844},"regular":{"height":52,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/18/363290140e4b3fd0e01eae4d2cc3874d/e86cf2090d3eec989c5bb68ae6d3b0e6/lateximg.png","width":422}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"Let's identify the given amounts in the problem.\n\n| |2017 |2018 | \n|--|--:|--:| \n| Current Assets |$4,810 |$5,360 | \n|Current Liabilities | 2,230|2,970 | \n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":103,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/18/363290140e4b3fd0e01eae4d2cc3874d/aa2bd76b08fb7c8b9c122ead52fae380/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/18/363290140e4b3fd0e01eae4d2cc3874d/aa2bd76b08fb7c8b9c122ead52fae380/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"Before we compute for the change in net working capital, we need to compute first the Ending NWC using the formula below:\n\n $$ \\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Ending NWC} &= \\text{Current Assets 2018 } - {\\text{Current Liabilities 2018}}\\\\[5pt]\n&= \\text{\\$5,360} - {\\text{2,970}}\\\\[5pt]\n&= \\underline{\\underline{\\textbf{\\$2,390}}}\n\\end{aligned}$$","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":263,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/18/363290140e4b3fd0e01eae4d2cc3874d/3554ad1b1b1be78c92d56507aab16e3f/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":133,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/18/363290140e4b3fd0e01eae4d2cc3874d/3554ad1b1b1be78c92d56507aab16e3f/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"Next, we need to calculate the Beginning NWC using the formula below:\n\n $$ \\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Beginning NWC} &= \\text{Current Assets 2017} - {\\text{Current Liabilities 2017}}\\\\[5pt]\n&= \\text{\\$4,810} - {\\text{2,230}}\\\\[5pt]\n&= \\underline{\\underline{\\textbf{\\$2,580}}}\n\\end{aligned}$$","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":256,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/18/363290140e4b3fd0e01eae4d2cc3874d/d5e279ffd2c8441c60a7d0afdf64b2e9/lateximg_large.png","width":965},"regular":{"height":129,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/18/363290140e4b3fd0e01eae4d2cc3874d/d5e279ffd2c8441c60a7d0afdf64b2e9/lateximg.png","width":482}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":6},{"columns":[{"text":"Now that we have computed the ending and beginning NWC, let's now compute for the change in NWC using the equation in step 3.\n\n$$ \\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Change in NWC} &= \\text{Ending NWC} - {\\text{Beginning NWC}}\\\\[5pt]\n&= \\text{\\$2,390} - {\\text{2,580}}\\\\[5pt]\n&= \\underline{\\underline{\\textbf{(\\$190)}}}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nTherefore, the change in NWC is decreased by **$190**.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":7}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"a5ed0718-f165-4dda-94f7-b4a8b024afbe","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":7}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14880759,"exerciseName":"8","page":43,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"edb30281-ba18-49ee-80c3-e275b0df7697","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-2-questions-and-problems-8-edb30281-ba18-49ee-80c3-e275b0df7697"},{"id":14880760,"exerciseName":"9","page":43,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"a373d7f3-3e17-4d0a-8b55-ce148e27f27e","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-2-questions-and-problems-9-a373d7f3-3e17-4d0a-8b55-ce148e27f27e"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14880757,"exerciseName":"6","page":43,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"58735d85-1b22-4a77-abe5-1f84ff496643","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-2-questions-and-problems-6-58735d85-1b22-4a77-abe5-1f84ff496643"},{"id":14880756,"exerciseName":"5","page":43,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"00a1fd39-61d9-4617-ac73-830cd1818d7d","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-2-questions-and-problems-5-00a1fd39-61d9-4617-ac73-830cd1818d7d"}],"_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-2-questions-and-problems-7-8328b85b-f872-4963-9a3a-7008aaa7deef"}